{
  "texts": [
    "However, when no scents were detected, ants still showed limited exploration, often remaining near the nest rather than actively searching new areas.",
    "This indicated that while gradient following had improved, the exploration strategy was still inefficient in the absence of sensory cues.",
    "Using directional cues provided clearer guidance on responding to environmental gradients, resolving many inconsistencies observed in previous prompts.",
    "From Prompt 5 onward, ants became more adept at following pheromone and nest scent gradients, leading to a more organized foraging behavior.",
    "Despite these improvements, ants' exploration remained inefficient when no sensory cues were present, indicating a need for further instructions to promote effective exploration."
  ]
}